te_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` and `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` each rebuild the same `valid[\"is_new_possession\"]`, `possession_group`, and `F_t/L_t/N_t/M_t` pipeline instead of calling a shared function."],"suggestion":"Extract the shared play-by-play parsing and foul-context steps into one small module, then let each script keep only its task-specific orchestration. That would remove the copy-paste blocks and make the remaining code look intentional instead of generated.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"script_copy_paste"},{"dimension":"ai_generated_debt","identifier":"restating_comment_bloat","summary":"Several comments restate formulas or nearby code instead of explaining non-obvious choices","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","step2_build_possessions.py"],"evidence":["`calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py` starts `calculate_wmi_rawgame` with a three-line formula comment that directly mirrors the `m = f + (f * n)` and grouped mean calculations below.","`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` uses four consecutive comment lines to define `L_t`, `F_t`, `N_t`, and `M_t` immediately before the code that assigns those exact columns.","`categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py` and `step2_build_possessions.py` contain several narrative comments like `Defensive foul events only`, `score_difference = offensive score - defensive score at foul moment`, and `Keep only events where possession points to an actual team` that mostly paraphrase the next statement rather than documenting a tricky business rule."],"suggestion":"Delete comments that only paraphrase the code, and keep comments only where they explain why a rule exists or why a less obvious approach was chosen.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"single_edit","root_cause_cluster":"script_copy_paste"},{"dimension":